fields.engineering_tactics:
(1) Define onboarding as XState v5 actor with hierarchical states. CODE-LEVEL EXAMPLE (XState v5):
```typescript
import { setup, assign, fromPromise } from 'xstate';

type Context = {
  step: number;
  totalSteps: number;
  answers: Record<string, unknown>;
  archetype: 'magician' | 'caregiver' | 'hero' | 'jester' | 'sage';
  locale: string;
  adVariant?: string;
  planId?: string;
  error?: string;
};

type Events =
  | { type: 'ANSWER'; questionId: string; value: unknown }
  | { type: 'NEXT' }
  | { type: 'BACK' }
  | { type: 'SKIP' }
  | { type: 'PAYWALL_DISMISSED' }
  | { type: 'PAYWALL_PURCHASED' }
  | { type: 'RESUME'; saved: Context };

export const onboardingMachine = setup({
  types: { context: {} as Context, events: {} as Events },
  guards: {
    isLastStep: ({ context }) => context.step >= context.totalSteps - 1,
    isFirstStep: ({ context }) => context.step === 0,
    hasMinimumAnswers: ({ context }) =>
      Object.keys(context.answers).length >= 3,
  },
  actions: {
    advance: assign({ step: ({ context }) => context.step + 1 }),
    rewind: assign({ step: ({ context }) => Math.max(0, context.step - 1) }),
    persistAnswer: assign({
      answers: ({ context, event }) =>
        event.type === 'ANSWER'
          ? { ...context.answers, [event.questionId]: event.value }
          : context.answers,
    }),
    persistToDisk: ({ context }) => {
      // MMKV.set('onboarding_state', JSON.stringify(context));
    },
    emitTelemetry: ({ context, event }) => {
      // analytics.track('onboarding_step_completed', { step: context.step, eventType: event.type });
    },
  },
  actors: {
    fetchPersonalizedPlan: fromPromise(async ({ input }: { input: Context }) => {
      const res = await fetch('/api/onboarding/plan', {
        method: 'POST',
        body: JSON.stringify({ answers: input.answers, archetype: input.archetype }),
      });
      if (!res.ok) throw new Error('Plan generation failed');
      return (await res.json()) as { planId: string };
    }),
  },
}).createMachine({
  id: 'onboarding',
  initial: 'questionnaire',
  context: ({ input }: { input?: Partial<Context> }) => ({
    step: 0,
    totalSteps: 12,
    answers: {},
    archetype: 'magician',
    locale: 'en-US',
    ...input,
  }),
  states: {
    questionnaire: {
      on: {
        ANSWER: { actions: ['persistAnswer', 'persistToDisk', 'emitTelemetry'] },
        NEXT: [
          { guard: 'isLastStep', target: 'loadingPlan', actions: ['emitTelemetry'] },
          { actions: ['advance', 'persistToDisk', 'emitTelemetry'] },
        ],
        BACK: { guard: ({ context }) => context.step > 0, actions: ['rewind', 'persistToDisk'] },
        SKIP: { actions: ['advance', 'persistToDisk'] },
        RESUME: { actions: assign(({ event }) => event.saved) },
      },
    },
    loadingPlan: {
      invoke: {
        src: 'fetchPersonalizedPlan',
        input: ({ context }) => context,
        onDone: {
          target: 'paywall',
          actions: assign({ planId: ({ event }) => event.output.planId }),
        },
        onError: {
          target: 'planError',
          actions: assign({ error: ({ event }) => String(event.error) }),
        },
      },
    },
    planError: {
      on: { NEXT: 'loadingPlan', SKIP: 'paywall' },
    },
    paywall: {
      on: {
        PAYWALL_DISMISSED: 'softPaywall',
        PAYWALL_PURCHASED: 'completed',
      },
    },
    softPaywall: {
      on: {
        PAYWALL_PURCHASED: 'completed',
        PAYWALL_DISMISSED: 'completed', // soft = allow exit
      },
    },
    completed: { type: 'final' },
  },
});
```
(2) Hierarchical/compound states for chunked questionnaire: nest questionnaire > section_1 > question_1, etc. (3) Parallel regions: auth state, network state, push-permission state run independently of questionnaire state. (4) Guards prevent invalid transitions (cannot advance without answer for required question). (5) Actions = pure named side effects (persistToDisk, emitTelemetry, fetchPlan). (6) Persistence: serialize machine state on every transition (item 32) — XState v5 provides `actorRef.getPersistedSnapshot()` and `createActor(machine, { snapshot: persisted })`. (7) Cross-device hydration (item 33): server stores snapshot, client requests on auth, replays. (8) Visualizer: stately.ai/viz renders the machine for designer/PM review — single source of truth between code and product spec. (9) Tests: XState exposes `model.testPaths()` for property-based test generation covering every transition; @testing-library + xstate-test integration. (10) Server-driven UI (item 31) layered on top: machine config (states, transitions, guards) loaded from JSON payload at runtime. (11) Each screen subscribes to the actor via @xstate/react `useActor`/`useSelector`, renders FROM state.snapshot.value + state.context, dispatches events via send().
